The “Do No Harm, Plant a Charm” License (v1.0)

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this software to use, copy, modify, merge, or distribute it, subject to two conditions:

Don’t be evil. No military, surveillance, fossil fuel, or deforestation-related use. If your business model hoards digital attention to burn the planet, go away.

Rewild something. For every major deployment or derivative work, you must physically plant (or pay to plant) at least one native tree, seed bomb an abandoned lot, or restore one square meter of degraded land. A receipt, photo, or coordinates sent to https://kriteriscontact.blogspot.com/ suffices as proof.

This software comes with no warranties, but with the quiet hope that it outlives your server and becomes moss. Violators’ computers shall be haunted by the ghosts of extinct pollinators.